  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health, WASH and Protection Intervention</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to reduce the vulnerability of targeted conflict-affected communities by meeting their basic needs through Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH), Health and Protection intervention via 2 mobile clinics and 1 reproductive health center. The mobile clinics will offer primary health care services and work to identify Sexual and Gender-Based Violence (SGBV) survivors and transfer them to the reproductive health center for medical treatment and psychosocial support. The clinics will also provide individual psycho social counseling to both children and adults, conducted by social workers. The reproductive health center offers prenatal, antenatal and postnatal care care to women and newborns and helps support and educate women in making healthy pregnancy-related decisions and provides safe natural and C-section deliveries by qualified medical staff. The center will also raise awareness of sexual and reproductive health risks and conditions. WASH activities include offering access to safe drinking water by repairing damaged sewage systems and installing solar powered water purification units; educating beneficiary communities in water quality management; and emergency activities such as distributions of hygiene kits, jerry cans and potable water for IDPs.</narrative>
  </description>
